40 Ricketts Road Business Park is located in Mount Waverley, one of Melbourne's best known inner south-eastern business park locations. Situated approximately 15 kilometres from Melbourne's Central Business District, 40 Ricketts Road is conveniently located only 1 intersection from the junction of the M1 (Monash Freeway) and Forster Road. Ricketts Road and surrounding streets have seen extensive regeneration in recent years, now emerging as a hub for modern business parks and corporate headquarters. 40 Ricketts Road is another ING Real Estate development, which aims to deliver well designed and functional office and warehouse units with a modern and corporate appeal. The business park comprises 18 units ranging from 311sqm to 848sqm, aiming to provide an office and warehouse proportion that suits your needs.

This property is extremely well located in the heart of Mount Waverley’s industrial precinct, situated just 20 minutes* from the CBD via the Monash Freeway (M1), with the Forster Road interchange being just 600m* from the facility.

This well kept office has it all; functional fit out, good exposure, corner location, future potential and easy access to major arterial roads.
The property is located on the corner of Ricketts and Gilby Road.

Key attributes include:
- Office: 655sqm*
- Storage: 167sqm*
- Ample car parking
- 15-20 minutes from Melbourne's CBD.
- Combination of partitioned offices / meeting rooms
- Plug and play option

Ideally suited for organisations that are looking for good quality office accommodation without the price tag!

21 Ricketts Road, Mount Waverley is a unique offering with significant future upside, and one which CBRE strongly recommends for your consideration.

The surrounding properties predominantly comprise a mix of modern and older style commercial and industrial buildings. There is convenient access to the Monash freeway, connecting to the City and the outer eastern suburbs via Citylink and Eastlink. With Camberwell, Hawthorn, Toorak and Chadstone a short drive away, this makes for the ideal business location.

The functional properties comprise of three separate units, being two premium grade offices on the first floor and a ground floor café. Both the office units and the cafe have been fitted-out to an extremely high standard. The properties are to be sold individually or as a ready-made portfolio of three.
Strong depreciation allowances together with the robust tenant’s covenants make this opportunity an ideal addition to any investment portfolio.

CBRE is pleased to offer 77-97 Ricketts Road, Mt Waverley for sale via Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 29th September 2021 at 3pm AEST.
 
The site is situated in arguably the best Industrial location in the South East with two diamond interchanges on Blackburn Road and Forster Road providing immediate access to the Monash Freeway which connects users to the CBD and to Eastlink. 
 
The site itself has flexible special use zoning (SUZ6) which has seen the Monash precinct evolve over the past 10 years from a predominant industrial precinct to a mix of industrial, commercial and medical/healthcare development.
 
-	Total building area: 8,048 sqm*
-	Total land area: 15,100 sqm*
-	Over 139 meters* of exposure to the Monash Freeway
-	Two level corporate offices and amenities
-	High clearance warehouse with 10 roller shutter doors
-	Large power supply
-	Crane provisions
-	129* Car spaces
-      Available partially leased or with vacant possession
-      Prime E-commerce/last mile delivery location within massive residential catchment
 
For sale by Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 29th September at 3pm AEST.
